 Presidency has on Friday reacted to canards making rounds that vice President Yemi Osinbajo’s powers were whittled down by President Muhammadu Buhari, following the sack of the former’s 35 aides. November 8, 2019 In "News" Reduction of political appointees in Nigerian VP, Osinbajo was a response to the general perception of an oversized and bloated workforce in the Presidency. November 8, 2019 In "News" By Johnbosco Agbakwuru PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari has decried what he described as ethnic and political interpretation to the recent reorganization in the office of Vice President Yemi Osinbajo which affected 35 of his (Osinbajo's) aides. Reports had it that 35 aides of Prof. Osinbajo were sacked on the orders of… November 16, 2019 In "News"